<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 03 at 3:18PM EDT  by NWS Columbia</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Calhoun and
southeastern Richland Counties through 345 PM EDT...
At 317 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
St. Matthews. This storm was nearly stationary.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
St. Matthews and Fort Motte.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
